
[1]spruce

   SPRUCE, a. Nice; trim; neat without elegance or dignity; formerly
   applied to things with a serious meaning; now applied to persons only.

   He is so spruce, that he never can be genteel.

             SPRUCE, v.t. To trim; to dress with great neatness.

           SPRUCE, v.i. To dress ones self with affected neatness.

    SPRUCE, n. The fir-tree; a name given to a species of evergreen, the
    Pinus nigra, which is used in families to give flavor to beer. It is
                used by way of decoction, or in the essence.
